		<td><b>RETROID - A New Game Boy Game</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi!<br /><br />Maybe RETROID, a Game Boy project I've just released, is of interest to you. I hope it is ok to post a Game Boy project it in this section. If it isn't, please accept my apologies and move it to the correct section.<br /><br />My goal was to create a Game Boy game that meets the technical standards of (early) commercial Game Boy titles, using only a few very basic development tools. The result is a Breakout clone that can be downloaded here:<br /><br /><a href="https://retroidgameboy.wordpress.com/" class="postlink">https://retroidgameboy.wordpress.com/</a><br /><br />RETROID is similar to Alleyway but adds some features from Arkanoid and other games to it (such as bonus items, better graphics, in-game music, boss battle etc.). The game was optimized for the &quot;real&quot; Game Boy hardware but can of course also be played via emulator. If you'd like to emulate, I suggest using BGB. Some other emulators tend to e.g. not play the sound correctly.<br /><br />Here are some screenshots:<br /><br /><img src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/s/welawgznvfzem0p/Screenshot%201.jpg" alt="Image" />     <img src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/s/ewuu38icaef9d5q/Screenshot%202.jpg" alt="Image" />     <img src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/s/y68k5synunzu365/Screenshot%203.jpg" alt="Image" />     <img src="https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/s/70l653txeyxryv4/Screenshot%204.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Have fun and enjoy the show!<br /><br />Jonas

		

		</td>
	</tr>
